Rating: 3
Wonderful and easy recipe! I also had no chili sauce so I substituted ketchup and 1/4 tsp ground red pepper. I also added 1 extra TBSP. of cider vinegar and substituted the orange juice for 3 TBSP frozen orange juice concentrate. I had enough leftover sauce to store and it stored in my fridge for 2 weeks until I used up the rest of it on pork tenderloin medallions. Absolutely delicious!

Rating: 3
Was looking for a new way to do chicken and found this recipe which looked easy enough-and I had all but one of the ingredients on hand, so I tried it. I substituted an equal amount of ketchup for the chili sauce, but it worked. We loved it, even my two finicky kiddos. We've made it twice in one week. Make extra to have cold the next day. Yum!

